This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the development of a new metric-learning based framework for Support Vector Machines (SVMs) and Multiple Kernel Learning (MKL) algorithms. It also experiments with these algorithms on benchmark datasets to observe predictive performance improvements. The paper also touches upon concepts related to computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE), which are all related to machine learning. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of within-and between-class distances, which is a topic related to similarity learning (cs.SI).
